HOLMES:
Grigori Andrev.

26:38.190 --> 26:39.885
He's the one
Leo strangled.

26:39.930 --> 26:43.195
I guess you can
cancel this.

26:43.230 --> 26:46.620
Last time I checked, dead men
couldn't pull triggers.

26:46.670 --> 26:49.935
GREGSON:
So, if he didn't shoot
at Leo Banin, who did?

26:58.680 --> 27:00.944
(insects buzzing loudly)

27:04.720 --> 27:06.779
(buzzing continues)

27:11.460 --> 27:12.984
That's a little loud.

27:13.030 --> 27:15.828
You know?

27:17.330 --> 27:19.423
(buzzing stops)

27:19.470 --> 27:21.335
Studies have consistently
shown that changes

27:21.370 --> 27:23.759
in one's surroundings,
background noise,

27:23.810 --> 27:25.903
even the angle from which
materials are viewed,

27:25.940 --> 27:27.828
can result in fresh insights.

27:27.880 --> 27:30.371
That was background
noise to you, huh?

27:30.410 --> 27:31.946
Were you able to reach
the Warsaw police?

27:31.980 --> 27:33.345
Yes.

27:33.380 --> 27:36.747
And I got a pretty good
idea why Vitaly Andropov

27:36.780 --> 27:39.044
changed his name
to Leo Banin

27:39.090 --> 27:42.082
and left Poland
in 2005-- he stole

27:42.120 --> 27:45.089
100,000 zlotys from
his Bratvian buddies.

27:45.130 --> 27:48.293
That's about 30
grand American,
give or take.

27:48.330 --> 27:51.060
Well, perhaps his past caught up
with him the other day.

27:51.100 --> 27:52.761
Anything from ballistics
of note?

27:52.800 --> 27:56.691
Not exactly what
we were hoping for.

27:56.740 --> 27:58.002
Those .45-caliber slugs

27:58.040 --> 28:01.908
taken from the scene
match perfectly to bullets

28:01.940 --> 28:04.079
that we pulled out
of a RICO witness

28:04.110 --> 28:06.271
last year-- the guy
was about to testify

28:06.310 --> 28:08.016
against the Russians.

28:08.050 --> 28:11.144
Rumor had it that Grigori
Andrev was the triggerman.

28:11.190 --> 28:13.715
But he was_ not the_ shooter
on this occa5ion.

28:13.760 --> 28:16.149
Unless you think

28:16.190 --> 28:18.420
he was doing target practice
before Banin

28:18.460 --> 28:22.123
garroted him.
No. The shots caused the crash,

28:22.160 --> 28:26.096
so they must have been ﬁred
after Andrev's strangulation

28:26.130 --> 28:27.961
as Leo fled the scene.

28:28.000 --> 28:30.901
Some third party must have
picked up the weapon and fired

28:30.940 --> 28:33.158
at Leo's motorcycle
as it sped away.

28:33.210 --> 28:34.768
Shots went wide,

28:34.810 --> 28:37.028
but they caused him
to swerve and crash.

28:37.080 --> 28:39.969
Is Joan up to speed
on all this?

28:40.010 --> 28:42.171
She's gone with
Detective Bell...

28:42.220 --> 28:44.108
to visit the Good Widow Banin

28:44.150 --> 28:47.517
and explain the true
circumstances of her
husband's death.

28:47.550 --> 28:50.189
So, the man
whose body you found,

28:50.220 --> 28:53.280
you believe he was trying
to hurt Leo?

28:53.330 --> 28:54.922
Him and a partner, yeah.

28:54.960 --> 28:57.190
We have reason to believe
that they were part

28:57.230 --> 29:00.028
of the same organization
your husband used to work for.

29:00.070 --> 29:01.389
This idea

29:01.440 --> 29:05.308
that Leo killed someone
right before...

29:05.340 --> 29:08.275
it's been so hard to live with.

29:08.310 --> 29:11.848
I tried to pray
for his soul, but...

29:11.880 --> 29:13.074
your partner

29:13.110 --> 29:14.475
turned out to be right.

29:14.520 --> 29:16.078
I couldn't forgive Leo

29:16.120 --> 29:20.147
for abandoning our faith.

29:20.190 --> 29:25.025
But now you say it
was self-defense.

29:25.060 --> 29:28.393
(sighs)
It's a relief.

29:30.330 --> 29:31.490
(clears throat)

29:31.530 --> 29:33.225
(phone ringing)

29:33.270 --> 29:34.532
(sighs)

29:36.070 --> 29:38.038
Dr. Hawes, anything to report?

29:38.070 --> 29:40.538
The garrote wound is exactly
as thick as the cuts

29:40.570 --> 29:42.504
on Leo Banin's hands.

29:42.540 --> 29:45.043
Wire from earphone buds,
ifI had to guess.

29:45.080 --> 29:46.377
And?

29:46.410 --> 29:48.310
The initial toxicology report
came back.

29:48.350 --> 29:51.148
It's interesting-- the deceased
was on a carefully managed

29:51.190 --> 29:53.988
mixture of anti-anxiety
and heart meds.

29:54.020 --> 29:55.908
Thing is, you don't just

29:55.960 --> 29:58.428
take a handful of fluoxetine
and a few ACE inhibitors

29:58.460 --> 29:59.927
and hope for the best.

29:59.960 --> 30:01.427
These are medications

30:01.460 --> 30:03.997
that can only coexist
in a delicate balance.

30:04.030 --> 30:06.419
Are you saying that Mr. Andrev
must have had a psychiatrist?

30:06.470 --> 30:08.529
Figured you might want
to track him or her down,

30:08.570 --> 30:10.299
see if they know
any of the names

30:10.340 --> 30:12.160
of the people he worked with--
any luck,

30:12.210 --> 30:13.529
maybe you'll even find
your shooter.

30:13.570 --> 30:16.175
(elevator bell dings)

30:16.210 --> 30:18.440
(phone ringing)
Sorry, Dr. Glassman
is still on a call.

30:18.480 --> 30:20.300
He may be a while.

30:20.350 --> 30:22.272
He understands we are part of
a police investigation, right?

30:22.320 --> 30:24.185
Dr. Glassman's office.

30:24.220 --> 30:26.142
Are you sure this
is the doctor

30:26.190 --> 30:28.078
that wrote the
fluoxetine scrip

30:28.120 --> 30:31.157
for Grigori Andrev?
Captain Gregson sent men
to Andrev's home.

30:31.190 --> 30:33.454
I'm told that Dr. Glassman's
name was clearly legible

30:33.490 --> 30:36.152
on his pill bottles.
Oh. I'm supposed
to meet Jen.

30:36.200 --> 30:37.929
I'm gonna have
to reschedule now.

30:37.970 --> 30:40.063
You spoke to her?

30:40.100 --> 30:42.239
About you? No.
This is not the kind of news

30:42.270 --> 30:43.362
you break over the phone.

30:44.410 --> 30:46.401
He may have died, you know.

30:47.540 --> 30:49.474
Tony.

30:49.510 --> 30:52.047
Knowing him,
it was something quite heroic.

30:52.080 --> 30:54.947
RECEPTIONIST:
Excuse me, I'm sorry,
but Dr. Glassman

30:54.980 --> 30:57.210
has an appointment
with a patient in five minutes.

30:57.250 --> 30:59.389
Maybe you could come back
in an hour?

30:59.420 --> 31:01.513
No, I'm afraid I cannot;
I will be dead by then.

31:01.560 --> 31:03.448
What?
I've been feeling a bit down;
I'm thinking

31:03.490 --> 31:04.957
of taking my own life posthaste.

31:04.990 --> 31:07.550
Ms. Watson here is
beside herself about it.

31:07.590 --> 31:09.899
Does that window open?

31:11.470 --> 31:14.894
I'm required by law to take you
back to see the doctor

31:14.940 --> 31:16.635
if you make a threat like that.

31:16.670 --> 31:20.561
But you already knew that,
didn't you?

31:24.210 --> 31:26.178
GLASSMAN:
Mr. Holmes, is it?

31:26.210 --> 31:28.474
You're a police consultant?

31:28.520 --> 31:30.943
Mm-hmm. This is my
partner, Joan Watson,

31:30.990 --> 31:33.481
and I'm pleased to say
she's just successfully
treated my depression.

31:33.520 --> 31:34.657
Oh, that's wonderful news.

31:34.690 --> 31:36.578
That means that
you can leave now.

31:36.620 --> 31:38.679
I apologize for lying, but
time is of the essence.

31:38.730 --> 31:41.449
We are in pursuit of a
member of a dangerous
criminal syndicate,

31:41.500 --> 31:45.425
the Rukovskaya Bratva.
You treated one of them:
Grigori Andrev.

31:45.470 --> 31:47.392
(quiet chuckle)
You're smart enough to know

31:47.430 --> 31:50.092
that threatening suicide
would get you in here;

31:50.140 --> 31:52.108
you're certainly smart enough
to know that

31:52.140 --> 31:56.031
doctor-patient confidentiality
prevents me from discussing...

31:56.080 --> 31:57.502
Any living patients,
yes, we know.

31:57.540 --> 31:59.371
But this one is dead.

31:59.410 --> 32:01.071
Strangled
by a male nurse

32:01.120 --> 32:03.076
he was attempting
to assassinate.

32:03.120 --> 32:05.680
What?

32:05.720 --> 32:10.555
Surely you're well acquainted
with Mr. Andrev's sociopathy.

32:10.590 --> 32:12.421
You must have half expected
this day to come.

32:12.460 --> 32:14.553
Dr. Glassman, we know
that you treated him.

32:14.600 --> 32:16.227
Your name is

32:16.260 --> 32:17.989
on the fluoxetine scrip.

32:18.030 --> 32:20.419
You have an obligation
to waive privilege
when there is

32:20.470 --> 32:24.429
legitimate concern
about a client's
criminal actIVIty.

32:24.470 --> 32:26.438
I'm-I'm sorry.

32:26.470 --> 32:28.677
I, uh... (chuckles)

32:28.710 --> 32:31.247
I didn't want to treat Grigori.

32:31.280 --> 32:33.043
He just showed up one day

32:33.080 --> 32:35.719
and said he had problems.

32:35.750 --> 32:38.685
When I realized what he was
and who he worked for,

32:38.720 --> 32:41.280
H was just
too afraid
to cut ties.

32:41.320 --> 32:43.254
He was very careful
about what he said here.

32:43.290 --> 32:47.283
He didn't discuss any of the
particulars about his work.

32:47.330 --> 32:49.548
But... there was one name

32:49.600 --> 32:53.092
that-that just came up
multiple times.

32:54.370 --> 32:56.065
Um, Marko Zubkov.

32:57.300 --> 32:59.439
I gathered that
he was Grigori's

32:59.470 --> 33:02.735
right hand for certain...

33:02.780 --> 33:04.645
jobs.

33:06.280 --> 33:08.373
You guys squared away
around back?

33:08.420 --> 33:10.570
We're just questioning
the guy, right?

33:10.620 --> 33:13.384
Is all of this
really necessary?
Well, you saw his sheet:

33:13.420 --> 33:16.287
extortion, racketeering,
three unsolved disappearances.

33:16.320 --> 33:18.220
Marko Zubkov deserves
the full treatment.

33:18.260 --> 33:20.421
He's what we call
a "bad guy."

33:20.460 --> 33:22.325
I don't know why
you're complaining.

33:22.360 --> 33:24.362
You make it work.

33:33.370 --> 33:35.076
Sasha Zubkov?

33:35.110 --> 33:37.305
NYPD. We're here for Marko.

33:42.620 --> 33:44.212
(TV Playing)

33:44.250 --> 33:46.480
Marko, you look cozy.

33:46.520 --> 33:48.351
Can I see that hand?

33:48.390 --> 33:50.119
(TV clicks off)

33:50.160 --> 33:51.627
What is this?

33:51.660 --> 33:53.719
It's a murder investigation.
A man you knew

33:53.760 --> 33:55.728
as Vitaly Andropov.

33:55.760 --> 33:58.228
Where were you
three nights ago?

33:58.270 --> 33:59.567
Sunday night?

33:59.600 --> 34:01.739
I'd rather not relive it.

34:01.770 --> 34:03.328
You're gonna have to.

34:03.370 --> 34:05.429
If not here,
then at the station.

34:05.470 --> 34:07.768
(clicks tongue)
Impossible.

34:07.810 --> 34:11.246
The doctors say
I'm not supposed to walk.

34:11.280 --> 34:12.645
What doctors?

34:12.680 --> 34:15.410
The ones who operated on me.

34:17.420 --> 34:19.581
You wanted to know
where I was Sunday night?

34:19.620 --> 34:21.383
I was in a hospital.

34:21.420 --> 34:25.254
Because Saturday night I was
mugged by a guy with a knife.

34:25.290 --> 34:27.349
I lunged for the bastard,

34:27.390 --> 34:29.096
he stabbed me twice.

34:29.130 --> 34:31.792
If you don't believe me,
please call the hospital.

34:31.830 --> 34:33.661
They'll tell you.

34:33.700 --> 34:36.294
I was there the whole time.

34:50.250 --> 34:52.514
(door opens)

34:52.550 --> 34:54.882
How did it go at the hospital?

34:54.920 --> 34:56.387
Well, Zubkov's story checks out.

34:56.420 --> 34:58.524
Three nights ago,
he limped into the ER.

34:58.560 --> 35:00.289
with two stab wounds to his leg

35:00.330 --> 35:02.252
and a tourniquet
tied just below his groin

35:02.300 --> 35:04.222
to stop some serious bleeding
from his femoral.

35:04.270 --> 35:06.363
Claimed he was mugged.

35:06.400 --> 35:08.231
What about the police report?

35:08.270 --> 35:10.636
There was not much to it.
Cops who came took a statement

35:10.670 --> 35:12.365
and a couple of pictures
of the wound.

35:12.410 --> 35:14.332
Zubkov didn't check out
until last night.

35:14.380 --> 35:16.473
How's it going here?

35:16.510 --> 35:19.206
There are over 70 men
with Bratva ties

35:19.250 --> 35:20.842
in the NYPD's photo
manager system.

35:20.880 --> 35:23.348
Those are only the ones
who've been arrested.

35:23.380 --> 35:25.519
The real number of Bratva men
in the tristate area

35:25.550 --> 35:27.711
would be difficult
to apprOXImate.

35:27.750 --> 35:30.787
The man who shot at Leo the
night of his deadly accident

35:30.820 --> 35:32.378
might not even be here.

35:32.430 --> 35:34.591
(sighs) Okay, that is...

35:34.630 --> 35:36.393
depressing enough for me.

35:36.430 --> 35:38.398
I'm gonna go to bed.

35:38.430 --> 35:42.469
Have you given any more thought
to the "dead Tony" idea?

35:42.500 --> 35:44.661
Okay, that is not an idea.

35:44.710 --> 35:46.666
That is just another lie.

35:46.710 --> 35:48.769
While I detest nothing more
than willful ignorance,

35:48.810 --> 35:50.937
I have come to believe
that in certain matters,

35:50.980 --> 35:52.868
ignorance bestowed
can be a gift.

35:52.910 --> 35:55.470
Your friend Jan-- she
seemed like a nice person.

35:55.520 --> 35:57.545
She deserves neither
shame nor heartbreak.

35:57.580 --> 36:00.481
Okay, first of all,
her name is Jen, not Jan.

36:00.520 --> 36:01.919
And regarding
shame and heartbreak,

36:01.960 --> 36:04.258
you should have
thought of that a year ago.

36:07.260 --> 36:09.399
You're quite certain
someone with Zubkov's injuries

36:09.430 --> 36:10.795
couldn't have snuck
out of the hospital

36:10.830 --> 36:12.798
for just a few hours?
Not without starting up

36:12.830 --> 36:14.536
the bleeding again
and not without being seen.

36:14.570 --> 36:16.492
Wouldn't be the first person
to sneak undetected

36:16.540 --> 36:18.735
from a hospital--
I've done it myself.

36:18.770 --> 36:21.637
Yeah. Well, you have
never had injuries

36:21.680 --> 36:23.568
like that.
Mm.

36:25.280 --> 36:27.271
This is the tourniquet?
Yeah.

36:27.310 --> 36:28.914
Probably saved
his life.

36:28.950 --> 36:32.283
We've been operating
under a misconception.

36:32.320 --> 36:34.652
I think it's possible
that the attack on Leo

36:34.690 --> 36:37.716
was not the first attempt
the Bratva made on his life,

36:37.760 --> 36:39.284
but the second.

36:40.290 --> 36:41.826
If I'm right...

36:41.860 --> 36:44.522
I may also know
who shot at him that night.

36:45.700 --> 36:47.520
GREGSON:
Thank you
for waiting,

36:47.570 --> 36:49.788
Mrs. Banin-- I know you've
been here quite a while.

36:49.840 --> 36:51.899
I owe you
more than patience.

36:51.940 --> 36:54.272
Your officers have
been very kind to me.

36:54.310 --> 36:56.505
They said you had
some questions.

36:56.540 --> 36:58.508
HOLMES:
We do.

36:58.550 --> 36:59.869
(sighs)

36:59.910 --> 37:01.309
All right.

37:01.350 --> 37:02.840
(clears throat)

37:02.880 --> 37:06.316
Is this... a man?

37:06.350 --> 37:08.557
Obviously it is a man.

37:08.590 --> 37:09.818
Good.

37:09.860 --> 37:12.658
Does he have a nose?

37:12.690 --> 37:14.419
Yes.

37:14.460 --> 37:16.599
Excellent.

37:18.830 --> 37:21.936
I don't understand.
Who was that?

37:21.970 --> 37:24.438
Why did you
show me his picture?

37:24.470 --> 37:26.563
Oh, come on,
you know Marko Zubkov.

37:26.610 --> 37:30.330
You saved his life when
he tried to kill your husband.

37:30.380 --> 37:33.543
(sighs) Do you
recognize... that?

37:33.580 --> 37:36.674
It's the tourniquet
you tied around Marko's
leg after Leo stabbed it.

37:36.720 --> 37:39.314
You know how we know?
Because of the fabric.

37:39.350 --> 37:41.352
It's the same as the drapes
in your living room.

37:41.390 --> 37:44.985
HOLMES:
We've been wondering
how the Bratva found Leo

37:45.030 --> 37:46.986
after so many years in hiding;
turns out the answer

37:47.030 --> 37:49.453
was right in front of us--
you told them where he was.

37:49.500 --> 37:51.024
You let Mr. Zubkov
into your home

37:51.060 --> 37:52.994
before you left
the other day,

37:53.030 --> 37:56.466
so he could lie in wait.
This was Saturday,
before the accident.

37:56.500 --> 37:59.469
HOLMES: Only Leo
turned out to be quite
formidable, didn't he?

37:59.510 --> 38:01.728
He was much more than
Mr. Zubkov could handle,

38:01.780 --> 38:03.600
even with the_ element
of surprise.

38:03.640 --> 38:05.870
Leo fought him off,
stabbed him in the leg,

38:05.910 --> 38:07.446
and fled.
You came home,

38:07.480 --> 38:09.016
expecting to find
a dead husband.

38:09.050 --> 38:11.018
Instead, you
find a mobster

38:11.050 --> 38:12.688
bleeding to death
on your floor.

38:12.720 --> 38:15.359
GREGSON:
The tourniquet you
rigged up from your drapes

38:15.390 --> 38:17.085
saved his life,
so congrats.

38:17.120 --> 38:18.985
You told us your
husband called you

38:19.030 --> 38:21.021
shortly before he died,
only it wasn't to tell you

38:21.060 --> 38:23.893
that he loved you-- it
was to tell you that
he'd been attacked,

38:23.930 --> 38:26.421
it wasn't safe, and to
meet him in Far Rockaway.

38:26.470 --> 38:28.665
HOLMES:
So you hatched a plan
with Grigori Andrev.

38:28.700 --> 38:32.830
He would get there
first, lie in wait,
you would meet with Leo,

38:32.870 --> 38:35.600
you distract him,
so that Andrev
could attack him.

38:35.640 --> 38:40.077
Must have shocked you to see
your husband in action,
dispensing with Andrev.

38:40.110 --> 38:43.443
Shocked and scared you,
'cause now he knows
that you're in on it.

38:43.480 --> 38:44.981
So you don't have a choice.

38:45.020 --> 38:47.989
As Leo flees...
you picked up Andrev's gun.

38:48.020 --> 38:49.510
WATSON :
You missed,

38:49.560 --> 38:50.982
but the shots fired
were enough

38:51.020 --> 38:53.659
to cause the crash and
kill an innocent woman.

38:53.690 --> 38:55.351
This is an outrage.

38:55.400 --> 38:56.992
I loved my husband.

38:57.030 --> 39:00.067
That man out there--
I've never seen_ him
before in my life.

39:00.100 --> 39:03.536
Right. So you won't
mind that he just saw you
looking at a picture of him,

39:03.570 --> 39:05.629
nodding in the affirmative to
questions posed by the police.

39:07.410 --> 39:09.401
Why are you doing this to me?

39:09.440 --> 39:11.943
Why do you try
to get me in trouble?

39:11.980 --> 39:14.073
The reason we had you waiting
so long this morning

39:14.110 --> 39:16.544
is because we needed time
to search your home.

39:16.580 --> 39:18.548
We got a warrant--
we found the evidence

39:18.590 --> 39:20.012
for the attack
on your husband.

39:20.050 --> 39:22.553
Bullet holes
in your wall

39:22.590 --> 39:24.080
and bloodstains
on your carpet.

39:24.120 --> 39:27.556
You covered the bullet holes
up With pictures, but...

39:27.590 --> 39:29.490
the bloodstains,
you missed a bit.

39:29.530 --> 39:32.795
No. If what you say is true,
there was an attack,

39:32.830 --> 39:35.663
these men, these mobsters,
they cleaned it.

39:35.700 --> 39:37.497
Oh, I'm sorry,

39:37.540 --> 39:40.464
they hung new stuff on your
walls and you didn't notice?

39:42.580 --> 39:45.777
You can either keep lying to us,

39:45.810 --> 39:47.778
or you give us Zubkov.

39:47.810 --> 39:49.949
You don't, we're
gonna let you both go,

39:49.980 --> 39:51.789
and we're just
gonna build our case.

39:51.820 --> 39:55.881
You can take your chances
with the Bratva on the outside.

40:01.160 --> 40:04.789
Leo had his secrets,

40:04.830 --> 40:07.469
but I knew enough; I forgave.

40:07.500 --> 40:09.832
That's what we are taught to do.

40:09.870 --> 40:11.599
But not him.

40:11.640 --> 40:14.063
He couldn't forgive
when he found out

40:14.110 --> 40:16.738
what brought me
to the church.

40:18.510 --> 40:20.842
I needed money when I was young.

40:22.650 --> 40:24.015
movies.

40:24.050 --> 40:27.087
To pay to come
to America,

40:27.120 --> 40:28.758
I had to.

40:28.790 --> 40:31.486
One of his friends,
he saw these films,

40:31.530 --> 40:33.680
and then...

40:33.730 --> 40:35.618
it was over.

40:35.660 --> 40:38.493
Leo asked me for a divorce.

40:38.530 --> 40:42.569
We put every penny
